***DCL (Data Control Language)***

Used to control access permissions.

1. Create User:
  CREATE USER sqladmin
  IDENTIFIED BY anupyadav;

2. GRANT: Give SELECT permission to user

  A. Grant Connect Privilege:
    GRANT CONNECT TO sqladmin;
  
  B. Grant Create Table Privilege:
    GRANT CREATE TABLE TO sqladmin;
  
  C. Grant Multiple Roles:
    GRANT CONNECT, RESOURCE, DBA
    TO sqladmin;
  
  D. Grant Unlimited Tablespace:
    GRANT UNLIMITED TABLESPACE
    TO sqladmin;
  
  E. Grant Table Permissions:
    GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE
    ON Employee
    TO sqladmin;

3. REVOKE: Remove SELECT permission

  Revoke Privilege:
    REVOKE CREATE TABLE
    FROM sqladmin;

4. Drop User:
  DROP USER sqladmin;
